{code}
 Set<SOAPPrincipal> results = new HashSet<SOAPPrincipal>();

        for (TermQuery query : queries)
        {
            List<SOAPPrincipal> termResults = performUserSearch(query);
            results.addAll(termResults);
        }

        return new ArrayList<SOAPPrincipal>(results);
{code}

will return a randomly ordered list. The set should probably be a TreeSet, and order each entry by name (or whatever logically sorts each of the constituent queries, if there is such a concept. If not maybe fullname?).

For example, allow overriding the crowd.server.url like so:

{code}
-Dcrowd.property.crowd.server.url=http://localhost:1234/crowd/services/
{code}

The current SOAP API only allows you to return Users and Groups without "extra" attributes, the current SOAP API needs the addition of two methods 

{noformat}
SOAPPrincipal findPrincipalWithAttributesByName(Token token, String name);
SOAPGroup findGroupWithAttributesByName(Token token, String name);
{noformat}

This was the default behaviour prior to 2.0
